yle="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">oundation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, European Commission, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and the Living With Environmental Change Programme</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unique </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">expertise in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">British </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">attitudes to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> climate change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, having</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">collected </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">multiple </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">empirical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">data </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sets </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of public</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> responses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> using both quantitative and qualitative methodol